HEADWORD: cacogenics
<hw>cacogenics</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the study of the operation of
factors causing degeneration in the type of offspring
produced.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dysgenics.</syn>⟦br⟧
